|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/09/2240214              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

holy_calamity writes "A Canadian firm has launched a device that can
track the gaze of multiple people from up to 10 metres away. Originally
developed at Queen's University, Ontario, they hope to sell it to
advertisers to allow them to [0]monitor how many people look at their ads.
Admittedly they are trying more benign stuff too like better hearing
aids, but I doubt that will make up for movie posters that make a song
and dance whenever you glance their way."

