| Shredded Secret Police Files Being Reassembled                     |
|   from the burn-the-papers-from-now-on dept.                       |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday May 09, @21:30 (Security)       |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/10/0024233           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

An anonymous reader writes "German researchers at the [0]Frauenhofer
Institute said Wednesday that they were launching an [1]attempt to
reassemble millions of shredded East German secret police files using
complicated computerized algorithms. The files were shredded as the
Berlin Wall fell in 1989 and it became clear that the East German regime
was finished. Panicking officials of the Stasi secret police attempted to
destroy the vast volumes of material they had kept on everyone from their
own citizens to foreign leaders."

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/10/0024233

Links:
    0. http://www.ipk.fraunhofer.de/en
    1. http://www.komotv.com/news/national/7423656.html


