| A Chip on DVDs Could Prevent Theft                                 |
|   from the chip-the-children dept.                                 |
|   posted by samzenpus on Wednesday May 09, @22:49 (Security)       |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/09/2253205           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Dieppe writes "A simple [0]chip added to a DVD disk could prevent retail
theft. According to the AP article at MSNBC, the chip would be activated
at the register to make a previously dark area of the DVD clear, and
therefore readable. Could this help to stem the tide of the approximate
$400 million dollars in losses from brick and mortar stores? Game console
DVDs could also be protected this way too. Could this help to bring the
prices down on DVD games and movies?"

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/09/2253205

Links:
    0. http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/18577503/


