be951 writes "Democratic party leaders are seriously considering
[0]making the Florida primary 'nonbinding', meaning they could ignore the
actual vote by Florida democrats and allow party leaders to decide how
Florida's more than 200 delegates are divided up among the candidates. 'I
think it's much higher than 50-50 that we will make Jan. 29 a nonbinding'
election, said Jon Ausman, a veteran Democratic organizer in Tallahassee
and member of the Democratic National Committee. This is in response to
Florida's move to [1]an earlier presidential preference primary, which
scrambled the primary calendar carefully worked out by the two national
parties."

