| Germans Pursuing Kiddie Porn In Second Life                        |
|   from the can't-do-that-here-either dept.                         |
|   posted by kdawson on Thursday May 10, @13:05 (Role Playing (Games|
|   http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/10/164250         |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Several readers sent in links to the BBC, which has picked up news of a
[0]German investigation into child pornography in Second Life. A German
TV station captured images of two avatars, an apparent adult and an
apparent child, involved in sexual activity. The station also said they
had infiltrated a ring trading real-world child porn in SL. SL creator
[1]Linden Labs is cooperating fully with the investigation, they write on
their official blog: "Our investigations revealed the users behind these
avatars to be a 54-year-old man and a 27-year-old woman. Both were
immediately banned from Second Life." The German prosecutor's office
hasn't responded to Linden's offer of help in identifying the real-world
traders.

