| Time to End Microsoft's Patch Tuesday?                             |
|   from the plenty-of-time-for-trickery dept.                       |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday May 10, @13:44 (Security)             |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/10/1652200           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]buzzardsbay writes "Techtarget's resident security curmudgeon, Dennis
Fisher, is calling for an [1]end to Microsoft's monthly security patching
cycle. Fisher points out that 'a hacker only needs one unpatched system,
one little crack in the fence in order to launch a major attack on a
given network. The sheer volume of the patches Microsoft releases each
month makes it quite difficult for even the most conscientious IT
department to get every patch out to all of the affected systems in a
reasonable amount of time.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://it.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/10/1652200

