| Amazon Cries 'Uncle' to End IBM Patent Feud                        |
|   from the make-it-stop-make-it-stop dept.                         |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday May 10, @14:22 (The Internet)         |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/10/1653216          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]theodp writes "Amazon will [1]pay an undisclosed amount to IBM to
settle a long-running patent feud, and the two companies have agreed to a
long-term patent cross-licensing agreement. Information Week [2]wonders
if an insurance dispute prompted Amazon's settlement, noting that
Atlantic Mutual sued Amazon back in March to escape any obligation to
reimburse the e-tailer should it lose the case brought by IBM. Amazon had
[3]relied on Atlantic Mutual's backing in an earlier legal battle it
[4]waged against tiny InTouch. 'Amazon, whose chief executive, Jeff
Bezos, is a vocal advocate of patent reform, has had numerous patent
issues in the past. In 2005, the technology used in its 1-Click checkout
system came under scrutiny as potentially infringing upon a similar
product made by a small Virginia-based company called IPXL Holdings.
Meanwhile, the US patent system itself is experiencing growing pains as
Congress continues to explore the possibility of updating it to better
serve the needs of the 21st-century business world.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://yro.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/05/10/1653216

Links:
    0. mailto:theodp@aol.com
    1. http://news.zdnet.co.uk/itmanagement/0,1000000308,39287004,00.htm
