| Sounds Bring Google Earth to Life                                  |
|   from the just-avoid-the-howler-monkey-jungle dept.               |
|   posted by Zonk on Thursday May 10, @19:03 (Google)               |
|   http://slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/05/10/1648259              |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

Strudelkugel writes "The BBC is reporting that a Californian company has
created software that can [0]layer relevant recorded sounds over
locations in Google Earth. The firm, Wild Sanctuary, has thousands of
hours of recordings from all over the world. Company director Dr. Krause
has spent over 40 years collecting sounds from natural and man-made
habitats. '... his recordings include more than 15,000 animal noises, and
sounds from a huge array of habitats, including cities, deserts,
mountains and the marine environment. It is the largest library in
existence of natural sound, he said. He said the idea would be to zoom-in
on a particular area and then have the option to listen to the
accompanying sound.'"

